    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Me</h1>

        Wojciech Barczynski is a software engineering leader with over 18 years of experience as both a practitioner and manager. Previously VP of Engineering at Spacelift, he now serves on the Technical Steering Committee for OpenTofu and is an advocate for Infrastructure-as-Code.
        With a strong background in cloud native technologies and Golang development, Wojciech has led engineering teams at Codility, Hypatos (Fintech/ML SaaS), Lyke (fashion marketplace), and Cloud&Heat (IaaS with OpenStack). He holds a Master's degree from Wroclaw University of Technology and helps organize the Golang Warsaw Meetup.

        His passion for teaching and mentoring spans over 10 years, with more than 1000 didactic hours and 30+ public talks at conferences and meetups. Wojciech recently also joined <a href="https://app.theforem.co/mentors">the Forem</a> as a mentor.
        
